    "description": "Haribhakti & Co Holdings Services is actively seeking a talented and motivated Investment Banker to join our dynamic team in Ranchi. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Haribhakti & Co Holdings Services:\nHaribhakti & Co Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Com / M.Com / MBA Finance\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Ranchi, Jharkhand, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Haribhakti & Co Holdings Services!",
